scripts.text:
You emerge onto the freezing roof of the castle. The icy wind howls over the battlements behind you, strips of ragged cloud race past barely a few hundred meters above your head. The cold is almost unbearable.

You hunch deeper in your clothing and wonder what it is that you're doing here...

events.flavourText:
The hall receeds into darkness. Flickering torches shed little light and less heat. The cold inside the castle momentarily makes you gasp. The temperature is well below freezing, to be sure. But something else about this place makes your gut clench and chills you to the bone, something unnatural and terrifying that seems to be flickering just at the edge of your vision and the back of your mind.

You wonder if exploring here is such a good idea...

You survey the blasted and inhospitable landscape.

Shattered and tumbled rocks cover the ground and are piled up in impassable heaps around the level space that you are in. Tattered grey clouds race across an empty sky, driven by a freezing wind that moans relentlessly from the west. You shudder and draw your clothing closer around you.

To your right looms an evil looking castle, rough cut stone walls and battlements menacing the stormy sky, dark window slits peering vacantly at you like the eyes of a skull. Human skeletons litter the stony ground around it.

script.name: Castle Fangorn to Ruins Of Hail

events.flavourText: The pillar feels warm beneath your hand...
